(28, '2A81757C92', 'FB5467BC01', 'google-launches-an-october-2023-core-algorithm-update', 'Google Launches an October 2023 Core Algorithm Update', '278', 'Experience SEO excellence with The Walkers as Google unveils its October 2023 Core Algorithm Update, optimizing your online presence', '&lt;p&gt;Google is constantly updating its features and algorithms to improve search results. The latest update, announced on October 6, 2023, is designed to identify and reward high-quality content.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The update is focused on three key areas:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ol&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content quality:&lt;/strong&gt; Google will now give more weight to content that is informative, helpful, and relevant to the user&amp;#39;s query. This means that websites that produce low-quality content, such as clickbait articles or spun content, will be less likely to rank well in search results.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Google will also be looking for content that is written by experts in the field. This means that websites that feature content from guest bloggers or other writers who may not be experts in the topic may see their rankings decline.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Authority:&lt;/strong&gt; Google will also consider the website&amp;#39;s authority when ranking content. This means that websites with a good reputation and are trusted by users are more likely to rank well on search results pages.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ol&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The update is expected to have a significant impact on search results. Websites that have high-quality, informative content that is written by professionals in the field are likely to see their rankings improve. On the other hand, websites that produce low-quality content or content that is written by non-experts are likely to see their rankings decline.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;What is a broad-core algorithm update?&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;A broad core algorithm update is a significant change in the way that Google ranks websites in search results pages. These updates are typically made every quarter, and they affect all websites equally, regardless of their size or industry. In this update, the ranking may change or fluctuate within weeks. Patience is essential at this time.&amp;nbsp;Google has not released many details about the new algorithm update for October, but they have said that it is designed to improve the quality of search results by rewarding websites that provide high-quality, unique content and a good user experience.&amp;nbsp;This is the third core update of the Google algorithm this year 2023. The first was in March, then in August, and now in October.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/c7af6502c29362.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;How can I improve my website&amp;#39;s ranking in the new algorithm?&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Improving website ranking in this new Google algorithm is very easy; you just have to remember a few steps, and you will rank at the top of the search engine result pages.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Create high-quality and unique content.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Make your website mobile-friendly and tablet-responsive.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Optimize your website for relevant keywords.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Make good-quality backlinks from high-quality websites.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;How long will it take to see results from the new algorithm update?&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;It can take several weeks or even months to see the full impact of a broad core update. However, if you start improving and making changes to your website today, you will be in a good position to benefit from the update in the long term.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;What types of spam is the October 2023 algorithm update targeting?&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The October 2023 algorithm update is targeting a variety of spam types, including&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Cloaking: Cloaking is a technique where a website owner shows different content to Google than to human visitors. Such as to rank higher in search results for irrelevant keywords or to deceive users into visiting a malicious website.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Hacked websites: Hacked websites are websites that hackers have compromised. Hackers may inject spam content into hacked websites, or they may redirect users to malicious websites.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Auto-generated content: Auto-generated content is content that is created by software programs rather than human writers. Auto-generated content is often low-quality and spammy.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Scraped content: scraped content is content that has been copied from other websites without permission. Scraped content is often low-quality and duplicated.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The most important tip:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Avoid keyword stuffing. Keyword stuffing is the practice of overusing keywords in your website&amp;rsquo;s content to rank higher in search results pages. Keyword stuffing is a black-hat and spammy practice that can destroy your website&amp;#39;s rankings.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/1049434d877010.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Key Factors About Google Core Algorithm October Updates&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;User experience&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;High-quality and helpful content&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Expertise, Experience, Authority, and Trustworthiness (EEAT)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Progress tracking&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Continuous improvement&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Google&amp;#39;s new October 2023 update algorithms can be helpful for many online businesses and websites. You just have to focus on continued improvement, patience, and staying dedicated to SEO.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;Earlier Google Core Algorithm August update&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;August update of Google algorithms states that it will improve search results. And give more relevant results to its users. These algorithms have some loopholes. A core update can affect website performance negatively or positively.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Google&amp;#39;s new update can change all the rankings. The new update just focuses on the website content with all white hat techniques. August&amp;#39;s update was not as powerful as October&amp;#39;s.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/1ac89543971992.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h4&gt;How to improve Google search ranking&lt;/h4&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;To improve your search results after the core October update, Google recommends the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Pay attention to page performance.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;See what search terms brought users to this page.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;Compare and improve your search results with the content of your query provided by Google on its help page.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This will show you where your content falls short or is weak in answering people&amp;#39;s or users&amp;#39; questions. Use what you learn to pre-optimize your content to meet searchers&amp;#39; needs. Google warns that the improvement is not guaranteed to help and that no two pages have the same quality or guarantee in Google search.&amp;nbsp;Lastly, these Google updates of 2023 are planned to improve the user search experience, so always give relevant results to your audience and aim to convey value through your content.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h4&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h4&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;', 'published', NULL, '[\"16\"]', 1, '2023-10-07 12:16:02', '2023-10-07 12:29:18'),
(29, '11B7A62CFF', 'A8DA2E3909', 'israel-under-attack-gaza-hamas-fired-5k-rockets-at-israel', 'Israel Under Attack: Gaza Hamas Fired 5k Rockets at Israel.', '288', 'Stay informed on the latest developments as Gaza\'s Hamas launches 5,000 rockets at Israel. The Walkers brings you real-time updates on this critical situation, keeping you connected to the world\'s events.', '&lt;p&gt;Dozens of armed Hamas surprisingly attacked Ashkelon Israel from the Gaza Strip. Israel on Saturday declared war against Palestinians. Aiming to avenge the rocket fired at Ashkelon. Israel&amp;#39;s military already launched an air strike on Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;40 were killed and 600 wounded in southern Israel says Israel&amp;#39;s health minister. The rocket fire began from multiple locations in the Gaza Strip starting at 09:00 am local time (03:30 GMT) on Saturday and continued for nearly half an hour. Hamas&amp;#39;s top military commander, Mohammed Deif, later announced in Hamas the start of military operations and called on Palestinians everywhere to protest.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Deif said that the launch of the missile was the beginning of the &amp;quot;Operation Masjid al-Aqsa storm &amp;quot;. According to the reports.&amp;nbsp;Deif said, &amp;quot;We decided to say enough is enough&amp;quot; and called on all Palestinians to oppose and protest against Israel. &amp;quot;Today is the day of the greatest war that will end the occupation of the world, adding that 5 thousand rockets were fired. The Israeli army told Israelis in the Gaza Strip to stay in their homes and not leave. It was warned that Hamas would pay a heavy price for its actions. Israeli media reported that the army shot dead passersby in the southern Israeli city of Sderot, and video posted on social media showed the Palestinian army fighting in border towns. Another video appeared on social media showing a burning Israeli tank.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/338e0f3bac3375.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Gaza Hamas takes captive to Israelis&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are unconfirmed reports that some Israelis were taken captive in Gaza. Israel responded with a wave of air strikes against targets in Gaza. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said that Israel is &amp;quot;at war&amp;quot; and Gaza&amp;#39;s ruler, Hamas, has to pay an unprecedented price. After dawn, the army fired a rocket over the fence from Gaza. The Israeli army said that many warplanes carried out air strikes on Hamas strongholds in Gaza and planned to evacuate thousands of people.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regional leader of southern Israel killed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Ofir Liebstein, head of the regional council in southern Israel, was killed in a clash with the Hamas. when he went to defend his community. According to Israeli media reports, rocket attacks continued throughout Saturday morning. To date, more than 5000 rockets have been fired at Israel. The injured are being treated in hospitals in the southern city of Ashkelon and the central city of Beersheba.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/1c022726583257.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;History of conflict between Israel and Palestine&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The conflict between Israel and Gaza is complex and protracted. The two sides have conflicted with the establishment of the state of Israel in 1948. The conflict is characterized by violence, displacement, and poverty on both sides. The origin of the conflict can be traced back to the British Mandate established in Palestine in 1922. The mandate was created to help establish a Jewish state in Palestine. However, the Institution also recognizes the right of Palestinian Arabs to live in Palestine. Conflicts between Jewish and Palestinian communities increased in the 1940s. In 1947, the United Nations voted to divide Palestine into two states, one Jewish and the other Arab state. The Jews accepted the plan, but the Palestinian community rejected it.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In 1948, the British Mandate in Palestine ended and the State of Israel was declared. Palestinians have declared their state, but it is not recognized by Israel and the international community. The 1948 Arab-Israeli War followed, in which Israel defeated a coalition of Egyptian, Syrian, Iraqi, and Lebanese forces. The war displaced thousands of Palestinians.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;After the war, Israel controlled most of Palestinian territory, including the Gaza Strip. Gaza remained under Egyptian occupation until 1967. During the Six-Day War in 1967, Israel captured the Gaza Strip from Egypt. Israel has occupied the Gaza Strip since then. The Gaza Strip is a densely populated coastal region with a population exceeding 2 million. The majority of the population consists of Palestinian refugees. Since 2007 the Gaza Strip has been blockaded by Israel and Egypt. The blockade has greatly affected the economic and humanitarian situation in Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The conflict between Israel and Gaza has led to violence, displacement, and poverty on both sides. Many attempts have been made to solve the problem but none have been successful. The conflict between Israel and Gaza is a complex problem with no easy solution. It is important to understand the history of the conflict to find solutions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/67d794bd779821.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h3&gt;International leader&amp;#39;s statement on the attack&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benjamin Netanyahu(Prime Minister of Israel):&lt;/strong&gt; He addresses the citizens of Israel we are at war and we will win the war against Hamas. He further added the enemy will pay the price he will never know. He said to follow all the instructions and the guidelines given by the government.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Rishi Sunak(Prime Minister of the United Kingdom): He says: &amp;quot;I am shocked by this morning&amp;#39;s attacks by Hamas terrorists against Israeli citizens.&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nHe continues:&amp;nbsp;Israel has an absolute right to defend itself. We&amp;#39;re connected with Israeli authorities, and British nationals in Israel should follow travel guidelines.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Narendra Modi(Prime Minister of India):&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;Deeply shocked by the news of terrorist attacks in Israel. Our prayers are with the innocent citizens and the families of the victims. We stand in solidarity with southern Israel at this misfortune.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;French President Emmanuel Macron:&lt;/strong&gt; I powerfully condemn the current terrorist attacks against southern Israel. I express my full solidarity with the victims and their families.&lt;/p&gt;', 'published', NULL, '[\"20\"]', 1, '2023-10-09 10:09:18', '2023-10-09 10:09:53'),
(30, '11B7A62CFF', '2D403F3F1D', 'israel-hamas-war-unraveling-the-ongoing-struggle', 'Israel Hamas War: Israel Allegedly Drops Poisonous White Phosphorus Bomb(Globally Banned)In Gaza After Hamas Attack', '295', 'Get the latest updates on the Israel-Hamas war, a long-standing conflict in the Middle East. Stay informed about the ongoing tensions, key developments, and international efforts for peace in the region.', '&lt;p&gt;White phosphorus ignites when it comes into contact with air and can burn human flesh. Air strikes that continue to bombard the Gaza Strip reports have emerged that Israel used poisonous White Phosphorus bombs in densely populated residential areas in Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In a statement, the Israel Defence Force has said that they targeted a structure that houses operatives and several of the military group operational command centers, including A 3-floor facility. Israel&amp;#39;s order to completely block Gaza includes electricity power, water, food, and fuel.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;They further continued that we are fighting against human animals. A total of 1300 Palestinians died after an air strike in the Israel Hamas war.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;US President Joe Biden approves emergency military aid package to Israeli occupation birth 8 billion dollar&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;President Biden affirmed US support for Israel in a phone call with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Saturday the White House announced. This morning I spoke with Prime Minister Netanyahu about the horrific and ongoing attacks on Israel.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Biden said in a statement the United States equally condenses this appeal assault against Israel by Hamas terrorists from Gaza and I made clear to Prime Minister Netanyahu that We are ready to provide all necessary support to the government and people of Israel.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/d4a34caed78798.webp&quot; style=&quot;height:490px; width:700px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;The U.S. deploys the largest worship in the world to assist Israel in the Israel Hamas war&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Washington AP Defence Secretary Lloyd Austin said Sunday he has ordered the Ford Career Strike group to sail to the Eastern Mediterranean to be ready to assist Israel after an Attack by a mass that has left more than 1,000 dead on both sides Americans were reported to be among those killed and missing.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The USS Gerald the navy&amp;#39;s newest and the most advanced aircraft career and its appropriate 5000 sailors and Deck of Warplanes will be accompanied by cruisers and destroyers in a show of force that is meant to be ready to respond to anything from possible interdicting additional weapons after reaching a Hamas and conducting surveillance.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Hezbollah targets Israeli observation points on the border&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Lebanon Hezbollah has claimed responsibility for a rocket attack on Shiba Farms an area occupied by Israel Saying it was in solidarity with Palestinian people. In retaliation, Israel fired at Southern Lebanon. Israel declared war against the Palestinian military and Hamar after they initiated a rapid military operation against Israel. More than 2,500 people have been killed on both sides since the Israel Hamas war started.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Israeli rocket hitting the residents of Palestinians&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu vowed to exact huge vengeance for this wicked day Israel&amp;#39;s air strike on Gaza began soon after the Hamas attack. they continue overnight and into Sunday destroying what is right claims are the groups of a training camp and homes among the other buildings.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Israeli Military announced its fighter jet had destroyed 800 militant targets in Gaza. Gaza health ministry said Israel strikes hit civilian residential buildings and complexes such as mosques.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;United Nations has said the number of these displaced residents of Gaza has risen to more than 123,500 as a result of fighting between the Israeli Military and Hamas with the number expected to rise in the Israel Hamas war.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/c425086bd44363.webp&quot; style=&quot;height:490px; width:700px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Israel increased air strikes on civilians in Palestine&amp;#39;s Gaza&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Israel enters Gaza and steals all the food and water supplies from Gaza. The Israeli army said it had taken control of most of southern Gaza following a Hamas offensive that surprised its army and intelligence agencies and led to the first road conflict in a decade. Hamas and other Palestinian forces in Gaza say they have captured more than 130 soldiers and civilians captured from Israeli territory. Israel sent tanks and drones to prevent violation of Gaza border fences to prevent new attacks.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Thousands of Israelis fled more than a dozen towns near Gaza and the army held 300,000 hostages; This is a huge increase in a short time. This move, along with Israel&amp;#39;s declaration of war on Sunday, shows that Israel has turned its attack on Hamas and is threatening to cause further harm to the people living and suffering in Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Israeli army death toll reaches 200 in Israel Hamas war&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Israeli Army announced the death toll of 200 soldiers since the start of fighting between Hamas and the Israeli Military. The Times of Israel website reported that the Israeli army released another 38 soldiers killed in the fighting, bringing the overall toll to 200. However, the total number of Israeli soldiers killed is 1000 while the number of wounded is 3000 as per reports in Israel Hamas war.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/b1a3c7b55e1081.webp&quot; style=&quot;height:490px; width:700px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;The United Nations is struggling to help innocent civilians in Gaza&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The UN Palestinian Authority said on Tuesday that it has been struggling to accommodate over 187,518 Palestinians in Gaza displaced by ongoing Israeli air strikes as hospitals and schools that it runs across the Gaza Strip were damaged in the fighting. In its report, the organization stated that the 83 schools it operates in Gaza, which hosts approximately 137,500 people, have become overcrowded and that drinking water is limited in some of them. They worked to provide adequate wipes, cleaning equipment, and fuel canisters. Ongoing conflict is disrupting work in the small area and UNRWA said nearly half a million people were unable to receive food aid this week because they were forced to close its distribution centre.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;', 'published', NULL, 'null', 1, '2023-10-11 10:59:25', '2023-10-11 11:02:40'),
(31, '11B7A62CFF', '2F3C815E07', 'israel-hamas-war-live-update-news', 'Israel Hamas war live update news', '299', 'Stay informed with The Walkers\' live updates on the Israel-Hamas war. Our coverage provides real-time insights into this critical global event.', '&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heavy Israeli bombing in Gaza continues on the 5th day of the Israel-Hamas war:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;On the 5th day of the Israel-Hamas war, Israel&amp;#39;s bombing air strikes continued in Gaza Israel targeting residential areas such as the Mosque, Complex, and residential buildings in Gaza. Some people of Gaza are coming to the streets to save themselves but have no way to go as the air strikes are everywhere.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Israeli Army&amp;nbsp;claimed that they had killed 1000 Hamas fighters in Israel Hamas war&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Israel&amp;#39;s army says they have counted 1000 bodies of Hamas fighters in war.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Atleast 300 children were killed in Gaza after Israel&amp;#39;s air strike.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;At least 300 children were killed by Israel air strike in Gaza, Palestinian Health Ministry reported. The Palestinian health ministry reported that Israel&amp;#39;s air strikes have destroyed 48 schools,10 hospitals, and 22,600 residential units in Gaza since Saturday.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The U.S. is considering deploying a 2nd aircraft carrier near Israel.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;On Saturday President Biden announced to help Israel with his military and provided 8 billion dollars to destroy Hamas. The president of the United States Biden then sent his second aircraft carrier near Israel to fight against Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Saudi Arabia calls (OIC the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Saudi Arabia prince MBS(Mohammad Bin Salman) calls for an urgent ministerial meeting of the organization of Islamic cooperation regarding the escalation in Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Putin&amp;#39;s ally Ramzan Kadyrov offered to send his Army to fight alongside Palestinians.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Chechen leader Ramzan Kadyrov Declared his support for Palestinians and offered to send his soldiers immediately in the conflict between Israel and Hamas war.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Israel air strikes bombs target university campus in Gaza&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Israeli fighter have targeted lasted university in Gaza. Ahmed Orabi, the university official, said the intense air strikes completely destroyed some buildings of the university.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UN says has Gaza food and water supplies for12days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The UN Palestinian Authority told reporters it had less than two weeks of food and water to help more than 180,000 people seeking refuge in schools in Gaza. &amp;quot;We gave food &amp;amp; water to 11 children a day. The roads are closed, we have no phones, our network is under air strikes. It is very difficult to know what is happening,&amp;quot; said Jennifer Austin, director of the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in Gaza assistant &amp;quot;We rely on our workers, who are themselves refugees, coming out to help. The situation we are facing is unprecedented. We are not giving up on who will go,&amp;quot; she added.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ministry of Health Palestine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Ministry of Health Palestine Reported 950 palestinians has been killed and 5000 others were injured during the Israeli aggression against Gaza on October 11.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n	&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Israel warns Egypt&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n	&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Aid trucks reaching Gaza will be bombed says israel officials.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/7c3ffdd9d64783.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Israeli Army bombs Gaza-Egypt border crossing&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The rafah crossing between Gaza and Egypt has been targeted by 3 Israeli air strike in last 24 hours as Palestine in attempt to flee deadly Israeli air strike a rights group reported.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Rafah border crossing is a key humanitarian corridor used by the red Crescent to deliver aid to the besieged gaza strips, home to more than two million palestinians. it is currently the only gateway in and out of Gaza.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The air strike targeted the crossing follow Israeli Defence Minister Yoav Gallant&amp;rsquo;s announcement of a complete siege of Gaza, sealing it off from supplies of water, electricity, food and fuel.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In response the UN high commissioner of Human Rights Volker Turk stated on Tuesday that the imposition of total siege is prohibited under international law.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Four consecutive days of air predominantly targeted civilian infrastructure on the strip, and follow and unprecedented assault staged by Hamas on saturday, when 100s of Palestinian fighters stormed the boundary fence ringing Gaza by air, land and sea.&amp;nbsp;so far, at least 1,000 israelis and 900 palestinians have been killed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/60a54f3cc85902.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;The UNRWA destroyed by Israeli air strike.&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Headquarter of United Nation subsidiary in Gaza, the United Nation relief and works agency for Palestine Refugeein the near east(UNRWA) saw significant damaged by Israeli heavy bombardment of besieged enclave overnight. According to the UNRWA collateral attraction and direct damages has been recorded to at least 18 UNRWA facilities include Schools shelter and hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/68c865a1406748.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Palestine should have a separate state says Vladmir Putin&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, during a joint press conference with Iraq&amp;#39;s Prime Minister Mohammed Shia al-Sudani Russian President Vladimir Putin declared that the establishment of a Palestinian state is a &amp;quot;necessity&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;Putin said the Israeli-Gaza conflict, demonstrates the&amp;quot;failure&amp;quot; of United states policy in middle east.&amp;nbsp;He futher added I think many people of the world would agree with me that it&amp;#39;s a crystal clear example of the failure of United states politics in Arab world.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Putin claimed that Washington&amp;#39;s actions disregard the &amp;quot;fundamental interests of the Pale-stinian people.&amp;quot; He went on to state that instead of seeking out workable options, the US was trying to monopolize the resolution of the Israel-Palestine dispute, advancing its agenda, and applying pressure to both parties.&lt;/p&gt;', 'published', NULL, '[\"30\"]', 1, '2023-10-12 12:18:27', '2023-10-12 12:18:50'),
(32, '50B2E73D22', 'BB47B6BF94', '2024-presidential-candidates-who-running-for-office', '2024 Presidential Candidates: Who\'s Running for Office?', '308', 'In 2024, a dynamic mix of presidential candidates is vying for the White House. Stay updated with The Walkers for in-depth coverage on this pivotal election', '&lt;p&gt;As the United States prepares for the November 2024 Presidential Elections, it&amp;#39;s more than just the usual red-versus-blue showdown. The race is heating up within the Republican Party, and Joe Biden seems poised to challenge Donald Trump for the presidency. In the wake of the 2020 election that saw Biden take the helm, this upcoming contest has become a global focal point, drawing interest from numerous Democratic and independent candidates. Join us as we explore the exciting and complex landscape of American politics in the run-up to this crucial election.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Major Party Candidates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;There are17 candidates running for president of the United States in 2024: 12 Republicans, 3 Democrats, and 2 independents. Many of them are aware that Joe Biden, who campaigned for president in 2020, and Donald Trump are powerful characters. To take on Joe Biden, nine Republicans have qualified for their party&amp;#39;s debates. The American public is excited to see how the 2024 race plays out since it is shaping up to be an intriguing contest with well-known figures and fresh challengers. Joe Biden, Donald Trump, and a number of other Democratic and Republicans candidates on the list of candidates for the 2024 US Presidential Election is provided for your reference.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Democrats&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 Biden&lt;/strong&gt; President Biden is presenting himself as a defender of democracy and a stabilizing influence after the previous administration. He plans to highlight his bipartisan achievements and support for Democratic priorities in his re-election. Despite being the oldest president in U.S. history, his party fully supports him.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 Marianne Williamson&lt;/strong&gt; Marianne Williamson, author and former spiritual adviser to Oprah Winfrey, ran an unsuccessful 2020 presidential campaign. She advocated for a Department of Peace, reparations, and addressed deeper societal issues but also endorsed unverified medical theories in her campaign promises&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3 Uygur&lt;/strong&gt; The Young Turks creator Cenk Uygur is an advocate for liberal causes like a higher minimum wage, universal health care, and paid family leave. Despite having similar policies to Biden, he continues to be critical and questions the &amp;quot;natural-born citizen&amp;quot; criteria.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/be959227eb2162.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Republicans&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Donald Trump&lt;/strong&gt; Donald Trump is a well-known and controversial former U.S. president. He&amp;#39;s facing legal troubles and wants to run for president again in 2024. He falsely claims he won the 2020 election and plans to undo some of the current president&amp;#39;s policies. Many people are keeping a close eye on his actions and influence in American politics.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nikki Haley&lt;/strong&gt; Nikki Haley made headlines by being the first to challenge her former boss, Donald Trump, for the Republican nomination. She has been critical of Trump and called for a &amp;quot;new generation of leadership&amp;quot; within the party. However, she has not yet committed to supporting the eventual Republican nominee for the presidency.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vivek ramaswamy&lt;/strong&gt; Vivek Ramaswamy, an entrepreneur and conservative commentator, is running for the GOP nomination, positioning himself as an outsider in politics. He&amp;#39;s self-funded his campaign and aims to further the conservative agenda championed by former President Donald Trump, making him a distinct figure in the Republican field.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perry Johnson&lt;/strong&gt; Perry Johnson, a businessman with no previous public office experience, tried to run for Michigan governor in 2022 but got disqualified for not collecting enough valid signatures. He&amp;#39;s a proud supporter of Trump and would back him if he runs again. Johnson is known for his work in setting quality standards and describes himself as a problem solver and a quality expert.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Larry Elder&lt;/strong&gt; Larry Elder is a conservative radio host who ran for California governor in 2021 but didn&amp;#39;t win. He&amp;#39;s against abortion rights, mask mandates, and the Black Lives Matter movement. He hasn&amp;#39;t said if he&amp;#39;d support a particular nominee but has criticized Donald Trump and questioned his appeal to swing voters.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Asa Hutchinson&lt;/strong&gt; Asa Hutchinson, the former Arkansas governor, has been critical of both Biden and Trump. He thinks another Trump nomination would be bad for Republicans and asked Trump to step aside after legal troubles. When asked if he&amp;#39;d support Trump if he&amp;#39;s nominated, Hutchinson said he doesn&amp;#39;t expect Trump to be the nominee but plans to support the chosen nominee.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tim Scott&lt;/strong&gt; Tim Scott is the only Black Republican in the Senate from South Carolina. He believes the Republican Party needs a candidate who can reach both Republicans and those who don&amp;#39;t agree with them. Scott has criticized the Biden administration, describing the U.S. as a &amp;quot;nation in retreat.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ron DeSantis&lt;/strong&gt; Ron DeSantis, Florida&amp;#39;s governor and former U.S. representative, is seen as a strong potential challenger to Trump. He&amp;#39;s known for his pandemic response, immigration stance, and LGBTQ rights approach. DeSantis hasn&amp;#39;t directly gone after Trump and hasn&amp;#39;t revealed if he&amp;#39;d back Trump as the nominee. He&amp;#39;s more focused on criticizing the Biden administration and aligning with Trump&amp;#39;s positions.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chris Christie&lt;/strong&gt; Chris Christie, the former governor of New Jersey, ran against Trump for the GOP nomination in 2016. He&amp;#39;s switched between being a critic and an ally of Trump but is now&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;critical again&lt;/strong&gt;. Christie has stated that he won&amp;#39;t support Trump as the GOP nominee and believes he is a viable alternative to Trump.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mike Pence&lt;/strong&gt; Mike Pence, the former Vice President, was a loyal supporter of Trump until January 6, 2021, when a pro-Trump mob attacked the U.S. Capitol due to his refusal to overturn the 2020 election results. Before joining Trump&amp;#39;s ticket in 2016, Pence had a long political career, serving in Congress and as Indiana&amp;#39;s governor. As governor, he passed laws limiting abortion access and a controversial religious freedom law that LGBTQ advocates criticized. Pence has announced his 2024 presidential bid, highlighting his candidate platforms 2024 and election issues. He has criticized President Biden and indirectly Trump, while also stating he would support the eventual GOP nominee.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Doug Burgam&lt;/strong&gt; Doug Burgum, a two-term governor of North Dakota, started as a software entrepreneur and sold a company to Microsoft in 2001. As governor, he signed laws restricting abortion and limiting transgender health care for minors. He intends to use some of his own money for his campaign. Burgum hasn&amp;#39;t stated his stance on Trump or whether he&amp;#39;d support him as the GOP nominee.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Francis Suarez&lt;/strong&gt; Francis Suarez has been the Republican mayor of Miami since 2017, with strong election victories. He comes from a political family, and his father was also a two-term mayor of the city. Suarez has worked on luring tech companies to Florida, lowering crime, and highlighting climate change to appeal to moderate voters. However, he&amp;#39;s facing allegations of using his influence to benefit a real estate developer while receiving payments from the company, which his office denies.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will Hurd&lt;/strong&gt; Will Hurd, a retired CIA officer and former Texas congressman, presents himself as a &amp;quot;common-sense Republican&amp;quot; aiming to win back swing voters who&amp;#39;ve moved away from the party. He cites pressing challenges like China&amp;#39;s influence, inflation, and falling school test scores as his motivation to run. Hurd was first elected to Congress in 2014 and chose to retire before the 2020 election. When he left, he was the only Black Republican in the House.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Will Hurd, a retired CIA officer and former Texas congressman, presents himself as a &amp;quot;common-sense Republican&amp;quot; aiming to win back swing voters who&amp;#39;ve moved away from the party. He cites pressing election issues and campaign promises, such as China&amp;#39;s influence, inflation, and falling school test scores, as his motivation to run. Hurd was first elected to Congress in 2014 and chose to retire before the 2020 election. When he left, he was the only Black Republican in the House.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/7c3a81ee312800.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;Independent and Third-Party Candidates&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robert F. Kennedy&lt;/strong&gt; Robert F. Kennedy Jr decided to run as an independent instead of for the Democratic candidate. He is well-known for his anti-vaccine activities, distributing false information about autism, opposing COVID-19 regulations, and once controversially alluding to Nazi Germany. His political stance runs counter to his background in environmental law and has strained his political relatives.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cornel West &lt;/strong&gt;Renowned philosopher Cornel West has lectured at prestigious universities and is currently a professor at Union Theological Seminary. In particular, he criticized President Obama as a progressive activist. He&amp;#39;s taken a different political stance ,considering the People&amp;#39;s Party, Green Party, and ultimately running as an independent.&amp;nbsp;Former representative suarez and Will Hurd of Texas ended his campaign for the Republican nomination and endorsed Nikki Haley,&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Issues and Platforms&lt;/strong&gt; The key election issues in the 2024 USA election include abortion debates following a Supreme Court decision, economic concerns like inflation and student debt, immigration policies, foreign policy positions focusing on China and Russia, and support for Ukraine in its conflict with Russia. These topics will play a pivotal role in the upcoming election.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://thewalkers.org/mystorage/media/f29cf4d9b12420.webp&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h2&gt;2024 Swing States: The Battlegrounds That Could Decide the Election&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;List of Swing States in 2024&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In the U.S. presidential elections, a few crucial swing states often determine the outcome. In 2024, Georgia, Wisconsin, Arizona, and Nevada are key battlegrounds that could shape the results.&amp;nbsp;In the 2020 election, Joe Biden won with 306 electoral votes to Donald Trump&amp;#39;s 232, but three crucial states (Georgia, Wisconsin, and Arizona) were decided by tiny margins, making up 37 electoral votes. If these states had gone to Trump, it would have been a 269-269 tie. These states were decided by less than 1% of voters.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In the upcoming election, some states that used to be up for grabs have become more predictable, with Ohio and Florida leaning Republican and Pennsylvania leaning Democratic due to recent Democratic wins in the state. This sets the stage for an intriguing contest in 2024.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demographics and Voting Trends&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Key states like Georgia, Wisconsin, and Arizona were highlighted for their importance in the 2020 U.S election by Joe Biden&amp;#39;s victory there with a margin of less than 1%. These states are still in doubt when it comes to 2024.&amp;nbsp;According to the University of Virginia, the incumbent party benefits from its favorable low unemployment statistics. Nevada, which tends to lean Democratic, on the other hand, has&amp;nbsp;Ohio have swung to the Republican side, while Pennsylvania appears to be leaning Democratic in light of recent Democratic victories. The political environment for next elections is shaped by these states, which continue to have sway in American politics.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campaign Strategies and Ad Spending&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The 2024 U.S. election is expected to be a historic one in terms of election campaign tactics and ad spending. As reported by NBC News and AdImpact, a staggering $10.2 billion is projected to be spent on political advertising across all election categories. Notably, this figure exceeds the 2020 election&amp;#39;s record, even excluding the $800 million self-funded by Michael Bloomberg and Tom Steyer. The lion&amp;#39;s share, approximately $7 billion, is expected to be channeled into TV ad spending.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Crucially, swing states such as Arizona, Pennsylvania, Michigan, Nevada, North Carolina, Georgia, and Wisconsin will witness intense ad campaigns spending, constituting around 75% of total presidential election ad spending.The swing state advertising plays a significant role in the election campaign.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Candidates will employ various campaign strategies, including grassroots efforts, tailored messaging, and extensive candidate visits to key states for the ground game. This election is set to be a high-stakes and costly battle, emphasizing the pivotal role of ad campaigns and personalized outreach in the political landscape.&lt;/p&gt;', 'published', NULL, '[\"24\"]', 1, '2023-10-16 09:18:34', '2023-10-16 09:29:07');
